[[Image:MOMap-doton-Hollywood.png|right]]
'''Hollywood''' is an [[unincorporated area|unincorporated community]] in southern [[Dunklin County, Missouri|Dunklin County]], [[Missouri]], [[United States]].

==Demographics==
It is located less than a mile from [[Route 164 (Missouri)|Route 164]] about twelve miles south of [[Kennett, Missouri|Kennett]].

==History==
The community was founded in 1900 and it takes its name from holly trees in the area, prior to which it had been called "Klondike". Its post office closed in 1974 when its longtime postmistress, Mrs G.H. (Hettie) Brannum, retired. Its mail now comes from nearby [[Arbyrd, Missouri|Arbyrd]]. Until the 1960s there were four grocery stores, a cotton gin, grain elevator, and the church of Christ.

